          Why Most Stock Market Simulator Games Don't Work
        </h3>
        <p class="text-[var(--c-text-muted)] text-[16px] leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Most <strong class="text-[var(--c-text)]">stock market simulator games</strong> trade realism for engagement — stripping out the indicators, order types, and risk metrics that make trading education valuable. What you get is a simplified game that feels nothing like an actual brokerage platform. Stockade is built differently. Every tool mirrors what professional traders use: full candlestick charts with volume histograms, EMA 9/20/50 overlays, VWAP, RSI, MACD, and a complete order panel with market, limit, stop-loss, take-profit, and OCO bracket orders. This is a <strong class="text-[var(--c-text)]">trading simulator</strong> designed to build transferable skills — not just let you watch lines move.
